Folder Structure Description

C***/

This folder contains all intermediate and final results for subject C0003 in the avatar dataset.
It includes every processing stage output of the markerless lumbar asymmetry analysis pipeline.

▸ avatar_masks_skin_only/

Contains binary skin-region masks extracted from the full avatar images.
These masks are used in the preprocessing stage to isolate the torso and waist regions.

avatar_crops/

Contains the cropped upper-body (torso) regions from the avatar images, centered on the waist.
These cropped images are used as input for subsequent edge detection, left–right reflection alignment, and asymmetry metric computation.

▸ edges/

Stores the left and right waist contour (edge) coordinates and their corresponding visualization images.

▸ torso_slices/

Contains separated left and right torso image slices, used for side-by-side comparison and alignment.

▸ trimmed_results/

Includes post-processed results after background removal and left–right torso alignment.

▸ R1/

Folder containing the final analysis results (Run 1).
This directory includes only two final quantitative indicators —
(1) area-based asymmetry and (2) Δx-based alignment deviation.
